@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - generativeai/Model
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Model spec, tracked status, and\ndelete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetModel;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListModels using filters compartment_id,\nbase_model_id,\nfine_tune_details.dedicated_ai_cluster_id,\ndisplay_name (+1 more);
:Create the OCI resource via CreateModel when\nno reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteModel with required via\nGetModel or ListModels to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetModel or ListModels\nuntil OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nDELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields base_model_id, compartment_id,\nfine_tune_details;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateModel only for mutable fields\ndefined_tags, description, display_name,\nfreeform_tags (+2 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: generativeai
slug: model
kind: Model
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update none;
delete DELETING
supported drift: defined_tags, description,
display_name, freeform_tags (+2 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
base_model_id, compartment_id, fine_tune_details
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_generative_ai_models filters
compartment_id, base_model_id,
fine_tune_details.dedicated_ai_cluster_id,
display_name (+1 more); exact compartmentId plus
baseModelId and
fineTuneDetails.dedicatedAiClusterId, with
displayName required when populated; blank
displayName skips reuse
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The generated runtime scopes ListModels by the
required compartment and only binds a unique
returned model that matches baseModelId,
fineTuneDetails.dedicatedAiClusterId, and any
populated displayName.
A service-local wrapper skips pre-create reuse
when displayName is empty and clears stale
tracked IDs before recreating so create never
guesses across older fine-tune jobs.
Create and update use read-after-write follow-up
through GetModel before the controller reports
steady state; the vendored SDK does not expose a
separate UPDATING lifecycle enum for Model.
In-place updates are limited to displayName,
description, vendor, version, freeformTags, and
definedTags; compartmentId, baseModelId, and
fineTuneDetails require replacement.
Delete retains the finalizer until GetModel
confirms DELETED or OCI no longer returns the
model.
end note
@enduml
